               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;Alternative classifications:
&lt;table class="table_lines"&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td title="MP"&gt;Peyrot&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td title="A1"&gt;archaic I&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td title="MM"&gt;Malzahn&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;–&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td title="TT"&gt;Tamai&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;–&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td title="TTC14"&gt;Tamai-C14&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;–&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to [[Broomhead I]]: 86, "The fragment is 2 1/2" [6.4 cm] long by 2 1/2" [6.4cm] deep". &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In [[Broomhead I]]: 92, there is no translation as such but a summary of the contents, thus: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a1 covers pāyti 18., where there is talk of a monk knowingly sitting or sleeping by force on a bed in the upper floor of a monk's dwelling. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 covers pāyti 19., where there is talk of a monk knowingly using water containing small animals to water the ground. ṣamāne lwāsācce (warsa) = bhikṣuḥ saprāṇakenodakena = [If] a monk [uses water] which contains small animals. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a4 covers pāayti 20., where there is talk of a monk wishing to build a large dwelling, he is allowed a second and a third time to repair the doors and windows to make them sound, but if he does it more than three times then there is pāyti. (tsa)ṅkṣalle postaññe = (vy)ādhiṣṭhā tavyā &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 covers either 21, 22 or 23, where there is talk of a monk going to teach the bhikṣuṇīs without having been deputed to do so. In this case if he doesn't return before sunset there is pāyti. Or if a monk should say that it is out of hope for gain that the monks preach to the bhikṣuṇīs. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 covers pāyti 24., where as in [ [[IOL Toch 117]] ], we see that it is a question of a monk making an arrangement with a nun to travel together, even if only to the next village. aśiyanaṃpaṣe = bhikṣuṇiyā sārdhaṃ&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I changed &lt;b&gt;b4&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;aśiyanampa= ṣe&lt;/i&gt; to &lt;i&gt;aśiyanampa ṣe&lt;/i&gt;. –Martin (Mon, 2019-05-20, 02:01:08 (CEST))&lt;/p&gt;</item>
